[SN]TITLE[SN]
Electric restored after Swansea power cut in the SA1 area

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
More than 700 properties in Swansea were without electricity for about an hour-and-a-half after a power cut in the SA1 area of the city.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Western Power Distribution confirmed 732 properties were affected when the power went down at about 15:45 GMT.
Engineers restored power just before 17:15 after fixing the fault.
The SA1 area covers parts of the city centre, waterfront restaurants, hotels, homes and apartments and the bay campus of Swansea University.
